Global Change Postdoctoral Fellowship program, administered by the University Corporation for Atmospheric
Research. We acknowledge high-performance computing support from Yellowstone (ark:/85065/d7wd3xhc)
provided by the National Center for Atmospheric Research’s Computational and Information Systems Laboratory,
sponsored by the NSF. We also thank Dr. Markus Jochum for sharing output from his MIS5e model simulation.
S.V. led the write-up of the manuscript and performed much of the analysis of model output. F.H. conducted the
model simulations and performed most of the post-processing. J.K. advised on the experimental design of the
model simulations and assisted in the write-up. W.R. developed the Early Anthropogenic Hypothesis, established
the model boundary conditions, and contributed to much of the write-up. P.C.T. contributed to the interpretation
of the orbital signature and observational data of MIS 19.
